nk:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531507\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531507\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 16, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104raw1665702975847.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/raw1665702975847.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/raw1665702975847.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"raw1665702975847\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Custom Database Connectors\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"raw1665702975847__custom_database_connectors_177820\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface provides DBMS connectors for many industry-recognized relational database systems, but you can also build your own. The use of connectors to support I/O interaction with DBMSs enables a Uniface application to be independent of the databases in use.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"raw1665702975847__p_d61865e1_d61866e1_d61867e1\">Database connectors are software modules that implement a well-defined set of functions for a particular DBMS. They translate Uniface I/O requests into the Data Definition Language (DDL) or Data Manipulation Language (DML) of a DBMS using the database's API.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"raw1665702975847__p_d61868e1_d61869e1_d61870e1\">The DBMS connector interface of the Uniface runtime system uses connector function calls to communicate with all the DBMS connectors. The connector itself communicates with the DBMS through the Application Programming Interface (API) of the DBMS.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"raw1665702975847__fig_d61871e1_d61872e1_d61873e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>DBMS Connector in the Uniface Architecture</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Diagram of DBMS Connectors in the Uniface Architecture\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/connectors2.jpg?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"raw1665702975847__p_d61877e1_d61878e1_d61879e1\">The library functions provided by the API define how to exchange data between the DBMS and the DBMS connector. If a query language is supported, the API defines the syntax and semantics of the language.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"raw1665702975847__note_w3924ab1b5c11_w3925ab1b5_w3926ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Ensure you are very familiar with the API of your DBMS before attempting to write a DBMS connector.</div>\n<p class=\"p\">If you want to use a transaction manager to control a database connector, you will need to\n         build a TM-capable database connector. Uniface does not provide TM-controlled connectors\n         and does not directly support third-party transaction managers. For more information,\n            see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xrb1665702976299.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrb1665702976299.html\" title=\"A database connector can be controlled by a transaction manager only if it is TM-capable. Uniface does not provide TM-controlled connectors and does not directly support third-party transaction managers. However, you can use the APIs provided by the Database Connector Interface to build a custom database connector that does.\">TM-Controlled DBMS Connectors</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531507\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531507\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Custom Database Connectors Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 16, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Custom Database Connectors Uniface provides DBMS connectors for many industry-recognized relational database systems, but you can also build your own. The use of connectors to support I/O interaction with DBMSs enables a Uniface application to be independent of the databases in use. Database connectors are software modules that implement a well-defined set of functions for a particular DBMS. They translate Uniface I/O requests into the Data Definition Language (DDL) or Data Manipulation Language (DML) of a DBMS using the database's API. The DBMS connector interface of the Uniface runtime system uses connector function calls to communicate with all the DBMS connectors. The connector itself communicates with the DBMS through the Application Programming Interface (API) of the DBMS. Figure 1. DBMS Connector in the Uniface Architecture The library functions provided by the API define how to exchange data between the DBMS and the DBMS connector. If a query language is supported, the API defines the syntax and semantics of the language. Note: Ensure you are very familiar with the API of your DBMS before attempting to write a DBMS connector. If you want to use a transaction manager to control a database connector, you will need to build a TM-capable database connector. Uniface does not provide TM-controlled connectors and does not directly support third-party transaction managers. For more information, see TM-Controlled DBMS Connectors . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}